<item>
            <title>[HBASE-3716] Intermittent TestRegionRebalancing failure</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-3716</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;See HBase-TRUNK build #1820&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This could be due to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-3681&quot; title=&quot;Check the sloppiness of the region load before balancing&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-3681&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-3681&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
In trunk, default value of &quot;hbase.regions.slop&quot; is 20%. It is possible for load balancer to see region distribution which falls within 20% of optimal distribution.&lt;br/&gt;
However, assertRegionsAreBalanced() uses 10% slop.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;One solution is to align the slop in assertRegionsAreBalanced() with &quot;hbase.regions.slop&quot; value.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
