                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13013569" author="jdcryans" created="Wed, 30 Mar 2011 18:34:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yeah the test should check against the same slop that&apos;s configured.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13013581" author="yuzhihong@gmail.com" created="Wed, 30 Mar 2011 18:54:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Also made changes to the return value of HMaster.balance().&lt;br/&gt;
Previously true was always returned even if there was no actual balancing action.&lt;br/&gt;
TestRegionRebalancing, TestMultiParallel and TestMasterObserver all pass.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13013582" author="yuzhihong@gmail.com" created="Wed, 30 Mar 2011 18:55:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;TestLoadBalancer passes too.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13014071" author="jdcryans" created="Thu, 31 Mar 2011 17:08:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This sort of operation can be done better:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;ret = plans != null ? true : false;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;All you gotta do is to take the return value of the condition and that&apos;s it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But even then you don&apos;t need to add an additional boolean since the next line is:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;if (plans != null &amp;amp;&amp;amp; !plans.isEmpty()) {&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Won&apos;t adding a &lt;em&gt;else&lt;/em&gt; statement in order to &lt;em&gt;return false&lt;/em&gt; be more readable?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13014076" author="yuzhihong@gmail.com" created="Thu, 31 Mar 2011 17:15:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Changed assignment of ret according to J-D&apos;s review&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13014082" author="yuzhihong@gmail.com" created="Thu, 31 Mar 2011 17:18:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;w.r.t. the second comment, I am not sure that we should bypass calling this.cpHost.postBalance()&lt;br/&gt;
I think the boolean return value should be passed to postBalance() as well. But that requires more changes.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13014092" author="jdcryans" created="Thu, 31 Mar 2011 17:37:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Good point, I didn&apos;t look carefully enough... mmm ok let&apos;s just keep the boolean, but please rename to something that better represents it&apos;s meaning like &lt;em&gt;balancerRan&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13014105" author="yuzhihong@gmail.com" created="Thu, 31 Mar 2011 18:01:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Revised again according to review.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13014129" author="stack" created="Thu, 31 Mar 2011 18:33:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed to TRUNK.  Thanks for the patch Ted.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13014307" author="yuzhihong@gmail.com" created="Thu, 31 Mar 2011 23:55:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Removed an unnecessary assertion.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13014402" author="stack" created="Fri, 1 Apr 2011 05:30:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I applied the addendum.  Thanks Ted.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13014913" author="hudson" created="Sat, 2 Apr 2011 01:15:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Integrated in HBase-TRUNK #1824 (See &lt;a href=&quot;https://hudson.apache.org/hudson/job/HBase-TRUNK/1824/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://hudson.apache.org/hudson/job/HBase-TRUNK/1824/&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="15017162" author="lars_francke" created="Fri, 20 Nov 2015 12:42:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This issue was closed as part of a bulk closing operation on 2015-11-20. All issues that have been resolved and where all fixVersions have been released have been closed (following discussions on the mailing list).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
